### 319.

<span class="margnote"> Proportions of the head seen in front
(319-321).</span>*a n o f* are equal to the mouth.

*a c* and *a f* are equal to the space between one eye and the other.

*n m o f q r* are equal to half the width of the eye lids, that is from
the inner \[lachrymatory\] corner of the eye to its outer corner; and in
like manner the division between the chin and the mouth; and in the same
way the narrowest part of the nose between the eyes. And these spaces,
each in itself, is the 19th part of the head, *n o* is equal to the
length of the eye or of the space between the eyes.

*m c* is 1/3 of *n m* measuring from the outer corner of the eyelids to
the letter *c*. *b s* will be equal to the width of the nostril.

